"12:30:7" : {s: 12, a: 30, w: 7, r: "رود", t: "تُرَٰوِدُ", l: "رَٰوَدُ", lc: 8, tl: "turāwidu", lb: "প্ররোচিত করা, প্রলব্ধ করা",e: "(is) seeking to seduce", b: "প্ররোচিত করেছে", f: 1, rm: "to seek, ask a thing gently, search (for food), go to and fro in a pasture, go round about. iradatun - will, free will. mirwad - axle of a pully. rawada - to long after, desire, seduce, entice, seduce against the will (with an) as in 12:126. yuridu - he wishes, intends. It is used as an auxiliary verb as in 18:77. The word iradah is used for power and capacity with reference to subjugation as well as to option and choice. ruwaidan - for a little while, go gently (according to some grammarians the word is a diminutive form of which verbal noun is not in use, it is used as sing. plu. f. m.)."},
